Kaduna State Governor, Malam Nasir El-Rufa’I yesterday appealed to the Chief of Air Staff (CAS), Air Marshal Sadiqque Abubakar to deploy its Special Forces to help check cases of kidnapping along Kaduna- Abuja highway. He also appealed to the CAS to establish another detachment in Kajuru Local Government Area of the state. Speaking at the commissioning of the 271 Nigerian Air Force detachment in Birnin Gwari, the governor commended the Emir of Birnin Gwari, Alhaji Jibril Zubairu Maigwari II for donating part of his land for the purpose. Earlier, the CAS said NAF for some time now has been involved in various internal security operations in the country, either alone or in conjunction with sister services.  El-Rufai urges air chief to deploy “special forces” to Abuja-Kaduna road Banditry: NAF Inaugurates 271 detachment in Birnin Gwari El-Rufa’i celebrates eid in Birnin Gwari, promises more security Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin